    {
      "id": "PopularPost139482",
      "post_content": "I play this card often, but I rarely get the chance to use her abilities. Her haste ability only matters on the turn you summon a creature, and I often just don't have the extra 2 mana. With a lot of white/red creatures already having first strike/doublestrike (and haste, for that matter), and plenty of better things to do with two mana then give a creature first strike, it just never seems to come up.  \n  \nEven so, it's nice to have the options, and a 2/2 for 2 isn't the worse thing to see in the world. I'm at least happy that she gives [Mother of Runes](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mother of Runes) haste on turn 3, though I usually try to drop mother turn 1.  \n  \nOne nice thing is that she's rather useful in multiplayer games. Offering a player to give their creatures haste is a nice bargaining chip, and making a battle between two other players go your way with selective use of her first strike granting ability is something that makes me wish she appeared more often in my multiplayer games.",
      "posted_by": "Asmodi0000",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost139482\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">I play this card often, but I rarely get the chance to use her abilities. Her haste ability only matters on the turn you summon a creature, and I often just don't have the extra 2 mana. With a lot of white/red creatures already having first strike/doublestrike (and haste, for that matter), and plenty of better things to do with two mana then give a creature first strike, it just never seems to come up.<br/><br/>Even so, it's nice to have the options, and a 2/2 for 2 isn't the worse thing to see in the world. I'm at least happy that she gives <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mother of Runes\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mother of Runes\">Mother of Runes</a> haste on turn 3, though I usually try to drop mother turn 1.<br/><br/>One nice thing is that she's rather useful in multiplayer games. Offering a player to give their creatures haste is a nice bargaining chip, and making a battle between two other players go your way with selective use of her first strike granting ability is something that makes me wish she appeared more often in my multiplayer games.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '139482'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\