    {
      "id": "PopularPost22292",
      "post_content": "Combat Damage works in a different way: if a creature with first strike or double strike is attacking or blocking, then there is the \"first strike combat damage\". After it resolves there is the \"regular combat damage\" where creature without first strike, creatures with double strike, AND CREATURE THAT DIDN'T COMBAT DAMAGE BEFORE deal their damages...  \n  \nNice card, but it could be far better if her abilities cost only ![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) and ![White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=W&type=symbol)...  \n3/5",
      "posted_by": "leomistico",
